cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper applies state-of-the-art techniques in deep learning and computer vision to measure visual similarities between architectural designs. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) model to achieve high accuracy in classifying works belonging to different architects. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep learning techniques to train the DCNN model. 
4. cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality): The paper deals with visual similarities between architectural designs, which can be applied in augmented reality and virtual reality applications. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses web scraped images and an original collection of images of architectural works to create a dataset, which can be used for information retrieval purposes.
